	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS




	(continued)



	 










	Incurred but not reported (“IBNR”) reserve estimates are generally calculated by first projecting the ultimate cost of all claims that have occurred and then subtracting reported losses and loss expenses. Reported losses include cumulative paid losses and loss expenses plus case reserve estimates. The IBNR reserve includes a provision for claims that have occurred but have not yet been reported, some of which are not yet known to the insurer, as well as a provision for future development on reported claims.  The following table presents IBNR liabilities and claims frequency, which is measured by claim event, for each accident year presented for the Program Services segment.




	 








	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 








	 






	    






	Total of incurred but not reported






	    






	 






	 










	($ in thousands)






	 






	liabilities plus expected






	 






	Cumulative number of






	 








	Accident Year






	 






	development on reported claims






	 






	reported claims






	 








	2007






	 






	$






	1




	 






	297,060




	 








	2008






	 






	 






	8




	 






	87,176




	 








	2009






	 






	 






	519




	 






