	The average annual percentage payout of incurred claims by age, net of reinsurance, is calculated using a weighted average of paid losses & loss adjustment expenses to incurred losses & loss adjustment expenses, both net of reinsurance for each age.  Program claims have a longer tail, therefore the percentage payout is calculated over ten years.  Lender claims have a short tail, therefore the percentage payout is calculated over two years.  The following tables that present the average annual percentage payout of incurred claims by age, net of reinsurance for the Program and Lender Services segments are required supplementary information and are therefore unaudited:




	 








	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 






	 








	 






	 






