	23. Business Combinations




	On September 30, 2016 (“the acquisition date”), the Company acquired 100% of the outstanding common shares of United National Specialty Insurance Company, which was subsequently renamed City National Insurance Company (“CNIC”).  CNIC is an admitted shell company with licenses in 49 states.


	   


	The purpose of the acquisition is to provide exclusive capacity for one of our programs.




	The acquisition date fair value of the consideration transferred totaled $18.7 million in cash.  The following table summarizes the fair values of assets acquired and liabilities assumed at the acquisition date.




	 










	 






	 






	 






	 






	 








