State National Companies, Inc. Key Developments

State National Companies, Inc. Announces Quarterly Cash Dividend, Payable on July 03, 2017
May 18 17
State National Companies, Inc. announced that its Board of Directors has declared a regular cash dividend of $0.06 per share payable on its outstanding common stock. The dividend will be paid on July 03, 2017 to all shareholders of record on June 19, 2017.


State National Companies, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Revises Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
May 10 17
State National Companies, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenues of $59.0 million, up 18% from $50.1 million in the first quarter of 2016. Net income was $11.5 million, or $0.27 per diluted share, in the first quarter of 2017, compared to net income of $9.7 million, or $0.23 per diluted share, for the same period in 2016. Income before income tax was $17.91 million against $15.08 million a year ago. EBITDA was $19.43 million against $16.63 million a year ago.

The company has raised the company's diluted adjusted earnings per share range from $1.13 to $1.21 to the company's new range of $1.18 to $1.26. The underlying assumptions for this range are: no anticipated realized investment gains or losses; an outstanding share count of approximately 42 million shares; an effective tax rate for the year of 36%; general and administrative expenses of $71 million to $75 million; net earned premiums of $140 million to $150 million; and ceding fees of $74 million to $84 million.


State National Companies, Inc. to Report Q1, 2017 Results on May 10, 2017
Apr 18 17
State National Companies, Inc. announced that they will report Q1, 2017 results at 5:00 PM, Eastern Standard Time on May 10, 2017


